set.int32

Class BLPIntHashSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • set.int32.LPIntHashSet
      • set.int32.BLPIntHashSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IntSet

    public class BLPIntHashSet
extends LPIntHashSet
    An implementation of Amble and Knuth's bidirectional linear probing table, with a simplified insert algorithm from A Concurrent Bidirectional Linear Probing Algorithm, and an original (but trivial) tombstone-free deletion algorithm. The keys (there are no stored values) must be 32-bit integers, which are permuted to form the hash codes (i.e., the "hash function" is reversible). This obviates the need to separately store hash codes or rehash the keys to perform operations which use hash codes.
